#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:2
msgid "string-repeat - multiply a string"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:9
msgid ""
"string repeat [(-n | --count) COUNT] [(-m | --max) MAX] [-N | --no-newline]\n"
"              [-q | --quiet] [STRING ...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:21
msgid ""
"``string repeat`` repeats the *STRING* **-n** or **--count** times. The **-"
"m** or **--max** option will limit the number of outputted characters "
"(excluding the newline). This option can be used by itself or in conjunction "
"with **--count**. If both **--count** and **--max** are present, max char "
"will be outputed unless the final repeated string size is less than max, in "
"that case, the string will repeat until count has been reached. Both **--"
"count** and **--max** will accept a number greater than or equal to zero, in "
"the case of zero, nothing will be outputed. If **-N** or **--no-newline** is "
"given, the output won't contain a newline character at the end. Exit status: "
"0 if yielded string is not empty, 1 otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:26
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:31
msgid "Repeat Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/string-repeat.rst:35
msgid ""
">_ string repeat -n 2 'foo '\n"
"foo foo\n"
"\n"
">_ echo foo | string repeat -n 2\n"
"foofoo\n"
"\n"
">_ string repeat -n 2 -m 5 'foo'\n"
"foofo\n"
"\n"
">_ string repeat -m 5 'foo'\n"
"foofo"
msgstr ""
